    "SSRewardText": "The couple tells you that the original purpose of the Golden Altar was to celebrate the arrival of the Great Bird, which was seen as a sunbeam of hope for the people of Aquarfall. However, nowadays, people honor the Great Bird there in the hope that it will bring them fortune and material wealth.\n\nThose who remember the true story leave some gold near the altar, always in the smaller pile, for others who may need it. As long as you take only what you need, you are free to collect some gold from there.\n\nAfter sharing the story of the Golden Altar, the couple decides to retire and rest before continuing their journey. You bid them farewell and continue exploring the temple.",

    "SSRewardText": "The couple tells you that the Thunder Altar is a place to honor the good omens the Great Bird brings to the people of Aquarfall.\r\n\nThey explain that the thunder aspect was once a test of valor and devotion for their ancestors, as they had to stand touching the altar for a whole day without being struck by lightning. Nowadays, however, you don’t even need to touch the altar! Simply standing close to it for a moment is enough. The couple then rants for a while about how the priests have become too lenient with their rituals.\r\n\nAfter sharing the story of the Thunder Altar and voicing their complaints about the new rituals, the couple decides to retire and rest before continuing their journey.     "SSRewardText": "The couple smiles when you ask about the Sacred Flame Altar, as they tell you it is the most spectacular of the Great Bird’s altars. The elders of Aquarfall were amazed by the Great Bird’s sacred flame, which burns its enemies and comforts its followers. It is said that thanks to this fire, the people were able to follow the Great Bird through the darkest nights.\r\n\nThe elderly couple explains that this is a favorite story of the priests. The Great Bird is like a peacock, but instead of feathers, its tail is made of flames, and the flames at its altar are just for display. They also mention that you could touch the statue at the altar with your fingertips without being burned!\r\n\nAfter sharing the story of the Sacred Flame Altar, the couple decides to retire and rest before continuing their journey. You bid them farewell and continue exploring the temple.",
